research_municipality_step.notes: The elected officials for Boyd, Texas, include the Mayor and six City Council members. The Mayor is elected at-large, and council members are elected from three wards, with two places per ward. Mayor and Place 1 seats are elected in odd years, and Place 2 seats in even years, all for two-year terms.
